OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA few showers to start in the
OL,6,Fwest, otherwise hazy sunshine on
OL,7,FThursday with blustery winds. Winds
OL,8,Feasing through the day and feeling
OL,9,Fpleasant in the sunshine.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA clear night with gusty
OL,12,Fwinds to start with but easing through
OL,13,Fthe night. Spots of rain in the far
OL,14,Fsouthwest. Staying mild with most
OL,15,Fplaces staying in double figures.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FA sunny start on Friday but
OL,18,Fturning cloudier in the afternoon.
OL,19,FAnother very warm day with an isolated
OL,20,Fshower in the afternoon, could turn
OL,21,Fthundery by the evening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
